🔬 “Phase transition” (grounded version)

What you’re intuiting can exist—but define it like this:

A phase transition = a nonlinear jump in measurable capability or behavior when inputs cross a threshold

Examples:
	•	sudden jump in task accuracy
	•	new capability emerging (not gradual improvement)
	•	cross-domain transfer appears unexpectedly

